# Anything the docker build doesn't need — keeps the build context tiny and,
# critically, makes `docker build` immune to permission-denied errors on
# runtime-created dirs (the container writes /data as root, which materializes
# on the host as root-owned via the bind mount in run.ps1 -Docker mode; the
# next docker build would then fail trying to tar those root:700 dirs).
#
# Anything that IS needed by the Dockerfile (bundle/, the Go source) must NOT
# be listed here.

# Runtime state written by the container — host keys, cookie secret, per-user
# carbonyl profiles, profile pictures, art gallery uploads. Persists across
# runs via the bind mount but is irrelevant to the image build.
data/

# Native build artifacts. The docker build does its own go build inside the
# alpine stage; the host's bin/ would just bloat the build context.
bin/

# Git metadata.
.git/
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# Editor / OS junk.
.vscode/
.idea/
.claude/
*.swp
*.swo
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Local docs that don't ship.
CLAUDE.md

# This file itself doesn't need to be in the build context either.
.dockerignore
